messages.message: This seems to break for opencensus, since it is from a git repo

```10:54:56  #13 3.807 Collecting opencensus@ git+https://github.com/instabase/opencensus-python@ec72cd39b431ec28ebcf72861852bccaef00c961 (from -r /tmp/requirements.txt (line 738))
10:54:56  #13 3.808 ERROR: Can't verify hashes for these requirements because we don't have a way to hash version control repositories:
10:54:56  #13 3.808     opencensus@ git+https://github.com/instabase/opencensus-python@ec72cd39b431ec28ebcf72861852bccaef00c961 from git+https://github.com/instabase/opencensus-python@ec72cd39b431ec28ebcf72861852bccaef00c961 (from -r /tmp/requirements.txt (line 738))```
Are we able to use 1.4.1 to generate without hashes?
You should be able to use `--without-hashes`
